      • makeIndustry

        public static EditableIndustry makeIndustry(java.lang.String name,
                                            java.lang.String commodityName,
                                            double output)
        Create a populated EditableSocialClass entity and also create its salesStock, moneyStock and consumptionStock
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the industry
        commodityName - the name of the commodity this industry produces
        output - the output that sells this industry is currently producing (i.e. at the time of project initiation)
        Returns:
        the populated EditableIndustry

      • editableIndustries

        public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<EditableIndustry> editableIndustries()
        Create an observable list of EditableIndustries (normally for display in the Industries Table) from the project identified by the current projectID and timeStampID. NOTE this is not just a wrapper. It will be edited by the user and eventually stored back to a modified version of the persistent entities from which it was created.
        Returns:
        an observableList of EditableIndustries identified by the current projectID and timeStampID
